18/09/2006
ZADAR, Croatia -- Prosecutor Ivan Galovic announced on Sunday (17 September) that a Croatian Serb, wanted by Croatian authorities on war crimes charges, was detained in the Greek city of Thessaloniki last week. Ernest Radjen, 47, is accused in connection with the murder of about 50 Croat civilians in Skabrnja and Benkovac in 1991. He reportedly has been living in Greece for over ten years. (Vjesnik - 18/09/06; HRT, HINA, AFP - 17/09/06)
